The paper deals with optimizing network throughput in a decentralized network with unknown and heterogeneous channel characteristics. This involves developing algorithms for optimal channel selection by multiple users, which falls under the categories of information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), machine learning (cs.LG), systems and control (cs.SY), and multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
